Full Title: Word, Utterance, Text in Cognitive, Pragmatic and Cultural Aspects 

Date: 26-Apr-2010 - 27-Apr-2010
Location: Chelyabinsk, Russia 
Contact Person: Conference Organizing Committee
Meeting Email: slovo@csu.ru

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; Cognitive Science; General
Linguistics; Language Acquisition; Translation 

Call Deadline: 15-Dec-2009 

Meeting Description:

The Faculty of Linguistics and Translation/Interpreting of Chelyabinsk State
University is glad to host the 5th International Scientific Conference Word, 
Utterance, Text in Cognitive, Pragmatic and Cultural Aspects on April 26th and
27th, 2010. 

Call for Papers

A wide range of theoretical and practical issues is to be discussed at the
conference:
- Cognitive science as a new paradigm of the 21st century.
- Linguistic world-image and cultural interaction.
- Discourse as the subject of interdisciplinary research.
- Semantics and pragmatics of text and language units.
- Current issues of translation/interpreting and foreign language teaching.

The Conference will include plenary and sectional meetings, a round table on
'Special Professional Training of Translators and Interpreters at Universities',
and workshops led by the leading specialists in the fields of
translation/interpreting and foreign language teaching.

The working languages of the conference are Russian, English, German, French,
and Italian. 

To take part in the conference please apply by e-mail at slovo@csu.ru before 
November 1st, 2009. Remote participation in the conference is also possible. 

An application should include full name (with a patronymic) of the applicant,
their academic degree and title, place of employment, telephone number, physical
mail and e-mail addresses, the topic of the presentation. Remote participation
in the conference is also possible.

Please submit the articles for publication (up to 6 pages in hard or soft
copies) before December 15th, 2009. Please consider the requirements for text
format - MS Word 6.0-7.0 document, font- Times New Roman, font size- 14,
interval- 1,5, margins- 2 cm, indentation- 1 cm (default setting). The title of
the article should be capitalized (alignment- center), the second line should
have the author's initials and last name (alignment - right), the third line-
the name of the institution the author represents. The article should also have
a 150-250-character summary in English (2-3 lines). The bibliography should be
at the end of the article in alphabetical order. The bibliographical references
should be put in square brackets in accordance with the State Standard (GOST)
7.0.5.- 2008... (???? 7.0.5.- 2008...)

Publication fee is 100 roubles (approximately $3) per page. Doctors of
Philosophy are exempt from publication fee. Payment information will be sent
with the second circular. For further information please inquire at 7 (351)
799-71-51 or 7 (351) 799-71-22. Mailing address - 129 Br. Kashirinykh St.,
Chelyabinsk, Russia, 454001, the Faculty of Linguistics and
Translation/Interpreting.

Accommodation is available at the Planeta Hotel at 37b Molodogvardeitsev St.,
Chelyabinsk.

Please note that the organizing committee reserves the right to deny the
publication of the articles that are irrelevant to the agenda of the conference
and/or are inadequately formatted. Participants or the institutions they
represent bear all the participation and accommodation related expenses. The
collection of the submitted articles will be issued prior to the beginning of
the conference.





